Quote: In ancestral terms, a customary right is the right to stand on the foreshore with an axe and defend it against all comers. The modern equivalent of that is the right of iwi authorities to be the representative voice taking submissions to the regional authorities or the Crown to protect the interests, which would <i>include</i> usage rights.
